  <h2>What Makes Replacement Different</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>The existing system.</strong> It has to be evaluated and worked around or removed.</li>
    <li><strong>Site history.</strong> How the property has been used affects the plan.</li>
    <li><strong>Design for today.</strong> A replacement is designed to current site conditions and needs.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Deciding to Replace</h2>
  <p>
    Replacement usually enters the conversation after repeated problems or a failed field — see <a href="/septic-repair-versus-system-replacement/">repair versus replacement</a>. When you are planning one, <a href="/request-service/">request septic service</a> to start with an evaluation.
  </p>

